# Axion EV Fleet Management: The Final Master Plan (Minor vs. Major)

This document outlines the definitive roadmap for taking the **Axion** platform from a 6th-semester Minor Project submission into a robust, enterprise-grade 7th-semester Major Project.

It is driven by the principle that the **Minor** must demonstrate a flawless foundational pipeline (data ingestion and real-time visualization), while the **Major** must demonstrate scale, state persistence, orchestration, and intelligence.

---

## 🏗️ Phase 1: Minor Project (6th Semester - Foundation & Core)
**Goal:** A flawless, real-time EV monitoring system that proves the core event-driven architecture works.
**Current State:** 90% Complete. 
**Directive:** *Do not add new scope.* Focus purely on fixing bugs, closing the final gaps, and polishing the demonstration.

### 🔴 Critical Bug Fixes (Must Complete Before Submission)
1. **Simulator Realism & Diversity**:
   - [temp_spike.py](file:///c:/CipherVault/Code/Projects/Axion%20-%20EV%20Fleet%20Management/Axion-Simulator/scenarios/temp_spike.py) is entirely empty. Implement the logic to spike battery temperatures to ~70°C.
   - [main.py](file:///c:/CipherVault/Code/Projects/Axion%20-%20EV%20Fleet%20Management/Axion-Simulator/main.py) ignores vehicle `profile` definitions in [fleet.yaml](file:///c:/CipherVault/Code/Projects/Axion%20-%20EV%20Fleet%20Management/Axion-Simulator/config/fleet.yaml). Fix the simulator so a Heavy Truck emits different baseline variables than a Standard Sedan.
2. **True Dual-Protocol Ingestion**:
   - The [MqttMessageHandler](file:///c:/CipherVault/Code/Projects/Axion%20-%20EV%20Fleet%20Management/Axion-Backend/ingestion/src/main/java/com/axion/ingestion/mqtt/MqttMessageHandler.java#10-32) lacks a Spring `@Component` annotation, meaning MQTT messages currently do not bridge to Kafka. Add the annotation and fix the Python [MqttEmitter](file:///c:/CipherVault/Code/Projects/Axion%20-%20EV%20Fleet%20Management/Axion-Simulator/emitters/mqtt_emitter.py#6-15) to send `json.dumps(payload)` instead of raw dicts.
3. **Data Integrity & Consistency**:
   - Unify the Health Status thresholds: Backend considers `< 50` as Critical; Frontend considers `< 60` as Critical. Standardize on the Backend threshold.
   - Fix case-matching inconsistencies (e.g., `odometerkm` vs `odometerKm`) between [TelemetrySnapshot](file:///c:/CipherVault/Code/Projects/Axion%20-%20EV%20Fleet%20Management/Axion-Frontend/src/services/api.ts#29-37) and the Canonical payload.

### 🟡 Missing Scope Items (To Build Immediately)
1. **Vehicle-Level Telemetry Charts**: Replace the snapshot text cards on the [VehicleDetail](file:///c:/CipherVault/Code/Projects/Axion%20-%20EV%20Fleet%20Management/Axion-Frontend/src/services/api.ts#38-41) page with Recharts line graphs showing the last 20 realtime data points for Speed, Battery %, and Temperature.
2. **Live OTA Proof-of-Concept**: The backend has basic OTA orchestration, but the UI is a placeholder. Wire up a simple "Trigger OTA" button on the frontend that calls the backend API and shows a "Simulated Success/Failure" toast.

### 🏛️ Minor Project System Architecture (Current State)
*Purely Volatile & Real-time (No Persistent Database).*
```mermaid
graph LR
    Sim[Python Simulator] -->|REST/MQTT| API[Spring Boot Ingestion]
    API -->|Key: vehicle_id| Kafka((Kafka: telemetry.normal))
    Kafka --> TwinUpdater[Digital Twin Consumer]
    TwinUpdater --> Redis[(Redis: Live State)]
    Redis --> Web[React Frontend: Live Polling]
```

